<p>The reason email wins is direct access. When you send an email, it arrives in the inbox. No algorithm decides whether your subscriber sees it. No competitor can outbid you for placement.</p>
<h3>Email List Size vs. Revenue</h3>
<p>A list of 2,000 engaged subscribers will outperform a list of 10,000 disengaged contacts every time. Quality beats quantity. Marketers who segment their email lists see 760% more revenue than those who send the same email to everyone.</p>
<p>The goal is not a big list. The goal is an engaged list that drives revenue.</p>
