<p>Calculate your growth rate monthly: (New subscribers - Unsubscribes - Bounces) / Total list size x 100. Track this alongside your total list size.</p>
<h3>The Quarterly Cleaning Checklist</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Remove all hard bounces (invalid addresses)</li>
<li>[ ] Tag subscribers inactive for 90+ days</li>
<li>[ ] Send a re-engagement campaign to inactive subscribers</li>
<li>[ ] Remove subscribers who do not re-engage after 2 attempts</li>
<li>[ ] Verify email addresses using ZeroBounce, NeverBounce, or similar tools</li>
<li>[ ] Check for spam traps (recycled addresses that flag senders)</li>
<li>[ ] Review and update segmentation tags</li>
</ul>
<p>A clean list of 3,000 engaged subscribers delivers more revenue than a dirty list of 10,000. Vanity metrics do not pay the bills.</p>
